The pig was not trusting of the pig however and was very reluctant to give the wolf any information on the house. The pig did however accept the compliment, and thanked the wolf. The wolf asked if he could go inside, to which the pig denied. "The inside is not done at this point yet. I would rather have it finished before showing anybody the indoors." said the pig. The wolf understood, but still could not get the house out of his head. He longed for house as beautiful and sturdy as the one that stood before him. If he had a home like this, he would be able to have total security whenever inside his home. Wolf was devious at heart, and knew that having the strongest house in the village only made him stronger as a villian. "Villian" was not really the word to describe wolf however during the day to day. The wolf simply had impulses that he needed to indulge in that caused him to become a villian. He was a villian because he was a wolf, and wolves were villians. It was in the wolf's dna to want to prey on weaker animals, however the wolf fights against this urge everyday. The wolf is a good person, but he has a bad side. Pig knew this, but simply could not trust him because he never knew when he would snap. Wolf grew lonely as the days went on, and he felt this home would bring him more friends and more happy times. The security was nice, but the friends were nicer.
